HQ? Miss?

248
00:12:23,291 --> 00:12:24,333
What're my orders?

249
00:12:24,416 --> 00:12:26,583
Let him wander
a bit more.

250
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:28,333
Follow him inside.

251
00:12:28,416 --> 00:12:29,875
[MAEKAWA] This is
Whiskey One, Maekawa!

252
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,875
Target is leaving the building!

253
00:12:32,958 --> 00:12:34,333
[AGENTS grunt]

254
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:35,500
[JUNICHIRO]
Hmm...

255
00:12:43,458 --> 00:12:45,000
[AZUMA]
Oscar One, Azuma reporting!

256
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:45,875
I'm sorry.

257
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:48,333
We lost sight of him in area D6.

258
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:49,875
That's bad news;

259
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:52,375
our target seems to know the
area like the back of his hand.

260
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:53,875
I expected nothing less.

261
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:55,416
If there were no
challenge to the chase,

262
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:58,458
then it wouldn't be
terribly amusing, would it?

263
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,625
[MALE ENGINEER] His mobile
GPS signal just went dark.

264
00:13:00,708 --> 00:13:02,458
He must have turned
off his phone.

265
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:03,791
Attention!

266
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:06,750
All units converge on his
last known location, D6,

267
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,625
and commence a
sweep of the area!

268
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:13,333
[AGENTS gasp]

269
00:13:13,416 --> 00:13:18,375
[AGENT panting]

270
00:13:20,541 --> 00:13:21,541
[JUNICHIRO]
Hm?

271
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,333
[AGENT A]
There he is!

272
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:25,083
[gasps]
Uh-oh!

273
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:27,375
[AGENTS panting]

274
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:29,708
So not cool!

275
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:32,916
[SUZUNE] 'Scuse me,
have you seen this guy?

276
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,208
[CLERK]
Uh. Oh, Kagami?

277
00:13:35,291 --> 00:13:36,958
He shopped a bit and took off.

278
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:40,000
I must have just missed
him then. Figures.

279
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:43,541
This is Yankee One, Suwa.

280
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:46,750
I have possible visual on
the target inside Oroden.

281
00:13:56,458 --> 00:13:58,291
[FEMALE OPERATOR] The target's
back is turned to the camera,

282
00:13:58,375 --> 00:13:59,541
we can't see his face.

283
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:01,833
Confirm it, but don't
make a scene.

284
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:06,000
[JUNICHIRO IMPOSTER]
Huh?

285
00:14:06,083 --> 00:14:07,125
What the--?

286
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:08,375
Negative!

287
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:09,916
[YONEKURA] Yankee Two,
Yonekura on the line!

288
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,833
We have eyes on our objective.

289
00:14:11,916 --> 00:14:13,541
[AGENTS grunting]

290
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:16,041
[JUNICHIRO]
Hm.

291
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,583
[AGENTS gasp]

292
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:18,791
[JUNICHIRO]
Hmm...

293
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,208
Pardon, may we have a
minute of your time, sir?

294
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:25,125
No can do, fellas,
I'm in a hurry today.

295
00:14:25,208 --> 00:14:26,166
I insist.

296
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,708
[YONEKURA grunts, gasps]

297
00:14:27,791 --> 00:14:28,750
What the-?

298
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:31,458
[AGENT C]
He's on the move again!

299
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:32,791
I've got some bad news!

300
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:35,916
We came into contact with
the target in Area D6!

301
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,250
Well, miss?

302
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:40,375
Our cover's blown, this is
no longer a covert op.

303
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:44,583
I advise granting our agents
permission to detain the target.

304
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:46,625
[JUNICHIRO] I don't have time
for all this running around

305
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:49,958
right now; I'm in danger
of being late as it is!

306
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:56,250
[DINERS, MAIDS chatter]

307
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:59,750
[MAID A]
Welcome home, master!

308
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,750
Who the heck
were those guys?

309
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:06,458
[JUNICHIRO] Hm. Bet that
Options girl sent them.

310
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:08,041
That would explain a lot.

311
00:15:08,125 --> 00:15:09,166
Well, in that case.

312
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,333
There's no reason
for me to hold back.

313
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:16,416
[KIKUKAWA] Yankee Three,
Kikukawa here.

314
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,833
I have visual on the target.

315
00:15:18,916 --> 00:15:20,958
Cross-reference with the
provided description.

316
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,375
Can you positively
I.D. the subject?

317
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:25,500
Verification is required.

318
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:27,375
[KIKUKAWA]
Why the increased caution?

319
00:15:27,458 --> 00:15:29,083
Because we're receiving
multiple reports

320
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:31,208
of sightings from agents
all over the grid,

321
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:33,083
and he can't be
everywhere at once.

322
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:34,375
[MIZOGAMI]
Tango Three, Mizogami.

323
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:36,250
I have visual in area D2.

324
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:39,625
[YOSHIOKA] Tango One, Yoshioka!
He's in F1! I repeat, F1!

325
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:41,708
He's even better
than I expected.

326
00:15:41,791 --> 00:15:43,583
And I expected a lot.

327
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:46,208
[SUZUNE] Man.
Where the heck could he be?

328
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:50,041
[SUZUNE] I thought he'd
be due for his fry fix.

329
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,666
Must've beat me there, too.

330
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,541
{GIRL B] We've gotta hurry,
or we'll miss it!

331
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:54,916
[SUZUNE]
Wait, is that?

332
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:04,833
[MALE OPERATOR]
What's the status on

333
00:16:04,916 --> 00:16:06,500
the facial recognition system?

334
00:16:06,583 --> 00:16:07,958
[ENGINEER]
It's not good.

335
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:09,333
As far as I can tell.

336
00:16:09,416 --> 00:16:11,541
The feeds are being
replaced by fakes.

337
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:13,083
But how?

338
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:15,500
[ENGINEER] I haven't figured
that out yet, but it looks like.

339
00:16:15,583 --> 00:16:16,958
He's hacking us!

340
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,416
[gasps]

341
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,000
[JUNICHIRO]
There.

342
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:22,208
Not taking no for an answer is
one thing, but trying to best me

343
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:26,083
in Akihabara of all places
is like an attack on titan.

344
00:16:26,166 --> 00:16:29,333
With time to spare, too.
I'm off.

345
00:16:29,416 --> 00:16:31,416
[FEMALE OPERATOR] He's breached
all of our firewalls!

346
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,833
[MALE OPERATOR]
Complete system shut down.

347
00:16:36,166 --> 00:16:39,333
He beat us. After everything
we did to find him,

348
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:41,583
he still managed to
get away from me.

349
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:43,541
Game well played.

350
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,583
[phone rings]

351
00:16:44,666 --> 00:16:47,458
[gasps]

352
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:56,166
I finally got a
personalized autograph

353
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,750
from Kanon "Sergeant
Saunders" Hanazawa!

354
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:00,666
--I could die of happiness!
--I've got you now!

355
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,833
[SUZUNE yells]

356
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:04,708
[JUNICHIRO gasps]

357
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:07,208
Well, look at this.

358
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:08,750
[JUNICHIRO]
Let me out of here!

359
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:10,291
You can't bag me up like this!

360
00:17:10,375 --> 00:17:12,958
[KOYOMI] Tell me, Suzune, how
did you manage to find him?

361
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:15,458
I used all of my resources
and came up dry.

362
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:16,708
I hate to admit it,

363
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:19,375
but being bested by both
Kagamis wounds my pride.

364
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:21,458
n
My bro's a shut
with only a few places

365
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:24,041
he's willing to go, so by
hitting up his usual haunts,

366
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:25,750
I discovered the
autograph signing.

367
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:28,291
It's his favorite show,
so I knew he'd come.

368
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:30,875
How funny. All this time
he was dodging my men

369
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:33,083
just to get some
girl's silly signature.

370
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,750
[JUNICHIRO] "Silly signature?"
I can't believe you said that!

371
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:37,500
This is a priceless
treasure to me!

372
00:17:37,583 --> 00:17:38,541
Bura-Kura is gold!

373
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,083
You'd better apologize!

374
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:41,041
[SUZUNE, JUNICHIRO grunt]

375
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,875
You'd better apologize!

376
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:46,041
Skipping your meeting like
that was hella rude, jerk!

377
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:49,083
How about we all just
calm down for a moment?

378
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:50,708
You know why we are here.

379
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:53,000
Have you considered the
offer to teach for my school,

380
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:54,166
Mr. Kagami?

381
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:55,291
[JUNICHIRO]
I refuse!

382
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:56,875
Aw, come on!

383
00:17:56,958 --> 00:17:59,625
[JUNICHIRO] In my one month as
a teacher, it became clear to me

384
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:01,875
that there's a critical flaw
in the education system!

385
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:03,166
Oh?

386
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:04,916
[JUNICHIRO]
It takes up too much of my time!

387
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,500
By spending all day
bettering others,

388
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:09,125
I was worsening my standing
in the anime blog rankings!

389
00:18:09,208 --> 00:18:10,333
[yells]

390
00:18:10,416 --> 00:18:11,375
[JUNICHIRO yelps]

391
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:12,666
[SUZUNE]
I'm so sorry!

392
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:15,750
This creature isn't fit
for educating humans!

393
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:17,916
[KOYOMI] It would appear that
without more drastic measures,

394
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,375
we will never see eye to eye.

395
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:20,958
[SUZUNE]
Huh?

396
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:23,666
I think a tour of the academy
grounds will help convince him.

397
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:27,666
[SUZUNE] You sure you really
want him on your payroll?

398
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,666
Well, I'm going to give
him a trial period.

399
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:33,041
Before I invite Mr. Kagami to
Hiiragi Academy's main campus,

400
00:18:33,125 --> 00:18:35,416
I want him to get his feet
wet at the Icho branch.

401
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,208
[gasps]
You're joking!

402
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:38,291
At my school?

403
00:18:38,375 --> 00:18:40,875
Hey! In case you forgot,
I'm right here!

404
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:43,000
And I'm not taking the job!

405
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:44,666
We finally arrived!

406
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:47,125
Welcome to Icho Academy.

407
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:56,416
Greetings, chairperson.
And what's this?

408
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,166
You brought along some baggage.

409
00:18:58,250 --> 00:18:59,583
Wow, impressive.

410
00:18:59,666 --> 00:19:01,625
We haven't been introduced
and she already hates me.

411
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,208
Thank you for your hospitality.

412
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:05,333
Would you be willing to
show Mr. Kagami around?

413
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:06,375
I refuse!

414
00:19:06,458 --> 00:19:07,208
Oh?

415
00:19:07,291 --> 00:19:08,041
[JUNICHIRO, SUZUNE gasp]

416
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:09,583
[MAKINA]
Of course not!

417
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:12,333
After all the hard work I put
into finding decent teachers

418
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:14,583
for this academy only
to have them rejected.

419
00:19:14,666 --> 00:19:17,791
You expect me to be okay
with you hiring some loser?

420
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:19,875
Alright, what's her deal?

421
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,375
Yeah, uh. She's the
kendo team captain,

422
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:24,458
a chairperson on the
student discipline board

423
00:19:24,541 --> 00:19:26,416
and she runs the
student council.

424
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,041
Makina Momozono.

425
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,625
[MAKINA grunts]

426
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:32,166
Are all those titles the reason
she gets to call me a "loser"?

427
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:35,083
Pretty much. She's Miss
Hiiragi's right hand man.

428
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:37,750
No one else has more
authority than her.

429
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:40,583
I read the report; this guy's
a self-indulgent, otaku!

430
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:43,041
I'll never approve of
this NEET as a teacher.

431
00:19:43,125 --> 00:19:47,791
But Makina. All the teachers
you do approve of are so boring.

432
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:48,958
So what if they are?

433
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:51,125
This is about education,
not entertainment!

434
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:52,708
That is true!

435
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:55,791
I'm afraid she's got me pegged.
There's no way a person like me

436
00:19:55,875 --> 00:19:57,375
is fit to teach
today's students.

437
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:58,666
What?

438
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,125
[KOYOMI]
See?

439
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:02,250
He's amusing, so he's perfect!

440
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:04,250
He's an unmotivated slacker!

441
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:04,791
[grunts]

442
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:05,875
[KIRIKO screams]

443
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:07,375
[MAKINA grunts]

444
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:08,291
[gasps]

445
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:10,375
[thud]

446
00:20:10,458 --> 00:20:11,416
[gasps]

447
00:20:12,291 --> 00:20:13,958
Well that hurt.

448
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:16,833
[gasps]
I'm so sorry, ma'am! Forgive me.

449
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:18,541
I got in your way, sorry.

450
00:20:18,625 --> 00:20:19,416
[JUNICHIRO]
Huh.

451
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:22,375
Why does she look familiar?

452
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:23,833
[MAKINA] Shouldn't you
be going somewhere?

453
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:26,375
Yes, ma'am. I was just leaving.

454
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:27,833
[JUNICHIRO]
What's going on?

455
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:30,583
This liar's on her way out
because she's been expelled.

456
00:20:30,666 --> 00:20:32,000
[JUNICHIRO]
Huh?

457
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:34,416
[MAKINA] She's been keeping a
part-time job in secret.

458
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:37,166
Thought we wouldn't find
out about it, but we did.

459
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,416
That's what she gets.

460
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,291
Man, private schools
sure are rough

461
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:43,833
if that's all it takes
to get the heave-ho.

462
00:20:43,916 --> 00:20:45,250
It's quite serious.

463
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,416
She was working in a maid café.

464
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,250
She could have at least
gotten hired somewhere

465
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:51,333
that wouldn't tarnish
the school's image.

466
00:20:52,375 --> 00:20:54,541
[JUNICHIRO]
Hmm.

467
00:20:54,625 --> 00:20:55,833
[grunts]

468
00:20:55,916 --> 00:20:58,000
[JUNICHIRO]
Hey! Tell me, what's the name?

469
00:20:58,083 --> 00:20:59,750
[KIRIKO]
I'm Kiriko Shikishima.

470
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:02,000
[JUNICHIRO] Not your name,
your maid café's!

471
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:03,916
Oh, it's called Heart on Heart.

472
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,500
It's in Akihabara.

473
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:07,333
Have you heard of it?

474
00:21:07,416 --> 00:21:10,208
[JUNICHIRO grunts]
Hmm...

475
00:21:10,291 --> 00:21:12,416
Pick up your stuff
and get back to class.

476
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,625
You're not expelled,

477
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:15,791
no matter what this
twin-tailed weirdo says.

478
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:18,791
Excuse me, but you have
no authority on the subject!

479
00:21:18,875 --> 00:21:21,083
And what do you mean
by "twin-tailed weirdo?"

480
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:23,625
[JUNICHIRO] Actually,
I have every authority.

481
00:21:25,541 --> 00:21:27,000
[KIRIKO]
Uhh...

482
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,750
[JUNICHIRO]
Effective immediately,

483
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:33,041
I'm a teacher at this school.

484
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,708
[ALL gasp]

485
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:36,875
[KOYOMI laughs]

486
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:38,500
[JUNICHIRO] If you
disrespect maid cafés,

487
00:21:38,583 --> 00:21:40,625
then you fail as head
of the student council,

488
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:42,333
Twin-Tailed Weirdo.

489
00:21:42,416 --> 00:21:45,416
Those two things aren't
even a little bit related.

490
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:46,541
There's something called

491
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:48,791
"maid dignity" and
I'm gonna show you.

492
00:21:48,875 --> 00:21:50,916
Prepare yourself for
your first lesson.

493
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,416
[gasps]

494
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,666
[JUNICHIRO]
Hm.

495
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:33,833
[MAKINA] This is
Makina Momozono speaking.

496
00:23:33,916 --> 00:23:36,625
Don't call me
"Twin-Tailed Weirdo," got it?

497
00:23:36,708 --> 00:23:39,041
In the next episode,
much to my dismay,

498
